product_name: MorpheWakeup Artist Under Eye Correcting Concealer
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganMorphe's lightweight, serum-infused Wakeup Artist Under Eye Correcting Concealer brightens, corrects, and smoothes the appearance of under eyes with a naturally radiant finish for comfortable all-day wear.
details: DetailsBenefitsBrightens, corrects & smoothes appearance of under eyesHydrating, non-drying formulaComfortable all-day wearKey IngredientsArnica, sweet potato extract, tremella mushroom, hyaluronic acid & glycerin known to hydrate skinResearch Results97% agreed the concealer erased the look of dark circles and brightened the appearance of under eyes*97% agreed the concealer instantly made them look more awake, rested, and refreshed**Based on a 33-subject consumer perception studyItem 2637327How To UseUse brush or sponge to softly pat concealer into skin or over color correcting concealer.For full coverage, use the doe foot applicator to swipe concealer onto your under eye and blend out with a sponge or brush.For a barely-there makeup effect, dot concealer in the inner corner of your eye and pat outward with a sponge.IngredientsWater (Aqua, Eau), Octyldodecanol, Propanediol, Glycerin, Diphenylsiloxy Phenyl Trimethicone, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Seed Oil, Polyglyceryl-3 Polyricinoleate, Isododecane, Acrylates/Dimethicone Copolymer, Glyceryl Caprylate, Sorbitan Isostearate, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Sodium Chloride, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Aluminum Hydroxide, Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Sodium Hyaluronate, Algae Extract, Arnica Montana Flower Extract, Tocopherol, Leuconostoc/Radish Root Ferment Filtrate, Tremella Fuciformis Extract, Pentylene Glycol, 1,2-Hexanediol, Fructose, Urea, Citric Acid, Sodium Hydroxide, Ethyl Hexanediol, Ipomoea Batatas Root Extract, Hydroxyacetophenone, Maltose, Sodium PCA, Sodium Lactate, Trehalose, Allantoin, Glucose. May Contain/Peut Contenir (+/-): Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499).

reviews.headline: Surprisingly good
reviews.comments: I gave this a try on a whim and I'm glad I did. Easy to apply and blend, good coverage. Goes on almost too glowy and takes a while to dry down. Stays just a tad tacky for a while. But once it dries down it stays put surprisingly well, even when I'm sweaty. Of course you can powder it down to speed that up but I don't usually. I'll definitely keep this one in my rotation!

reviews.headline: Impressive, Papaya made my very dark circles disappear
reviews.comments: I'm fairly new to color correctors. My go-to became a bit too dark for my dark skin tone, and was a bit too drying at times. I'm 60 now with dry-combo/mature/sensitive skin and very dark circles. Now that my skin is no longer normal, I have to use dewier formulas for everything, especially the eyes. I heard Morphe was a great choice for mature skin, and gave it a try. Papaya turned out to be my perfect shade. Practically makes my dark circles disappear. I could wear it solo without concealer for no-makeup makeup days, which is most days. Even better, the formula is quite dewy but not greasy, and blended out well. Didn't settle much in fine lines. I slapped it on to give it a try, but left it on for a few hours and still nice. Add a bit of bronzer to my cheeks and a lip gloss and I look rested, polished and fresh. I'll experimenting with using it with more makeup, possibly a bit of concealer dabbed lightly with a damp beauty blender. I used to think I needed full coverage concealer to cover my dark circles. But turns out I just needed a color corrector, and a little goes a long way. Try it!

reviews.comments: I'm really happy with my purchase. I originally bought the red color which was too dark but the apricot was perfect. It neutralizes the darkness under my eyes and I feel like it slightly brightens.

reviews.headline: meh... returned
reviews.comments: I wanted to love this because I adore so many morphe products, but this wasn't it. This concealer is kind of oily and so thin. If you aren't harboring dark circles from years of insomnia, I guess it would be OK? For me, it was not that girl.

reviews.headline: Perfectly Brightens Under Eyes
reviews.comments: I was looking for a concealer that could brighten under my eyes without setting into my fine lines and creases. Too many concealer tend to cake and just doesn't give me the effect I want. I decided to try this concealer, as I've always been pleased by the Morphe line and price point. This concealer did not disappoint! One dab was enough product for both eyes. The coverage was great, the brightening was perfect, and the concealer worked a full 8 hours for me. I'll definitely buy this one again.

faceoff_positive.comments:
As someone who has always struggled with hollow, dark under-eye circles, a good concealer is a must-have in my daily makeup routine. In fact, it's one of the most important steps for me. So when I heard about the Morphe Wakeup Artist Under Eye Concealer, I was eager to give it a try. I've had great experiences with other Morphe products, such as their brushes, highlighter gel, and Dripping lip glosses, but I had never tried any of their complexion products until now.

I have a medium-deep skin tone, and I chose the shade Toffee. It was the perfect match for my skin tone and blended effortlessly. I applied the concealer directly under my eyes without color correcting first, as I wanted to see how well it would perform on its own. The results were incredible! It felt like I had erased my dark circles entirely, and my under-eye area looked refreshed and brightened. The concealer offers full coverage, but it has a very natural finish‚Äînothing too heavy or cakey. I was pleasantly surprised at how lightweight and smooth it felt.

What impressed me the most was how the concealer provided the exact coverage I needed without making me look overly made up. My under-eye area looked much more awake, and I didn't get the usual comments throughout the day about looking tired!

The performance of this concealer rivals some of my high-end favorites, but without the steep price tag. I genuinely feel like I've found a high-quality product at a fraction of the cost. If you're looking for an affordable concealer that delivers great coverage and a natural finish, I highly recommend giving this under eye concealer a try. It's definitely earned a permanent spot in my makeup routine!
faceoff_positive.headline: My New Go-To for Bright, Fresh Eyes!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I have been in the market for a good concealer so I was excited when Morphe sent me this product in exchange for an honest review. I tried it as soon as I received it and was presently surprised by the texture and ease of application. I used this concealer daily in the humid Houston weather and loved how well it covered undereye circles and blemishes without being runny or tacky. This is honestly a great concealer that provider buildable coverage; however, I noticed that after about 3-4 hours of wear, the product began drastically creasing around my fine lines and sinking into my pores. I tried various combinations of foundations, primers, setting powders and setting sprays with this concealer to see if the creasing would decreased but to no avail. I do love this product and will continue to use it but only for special occasions or periods of time where I only need to wear makeup for a few ours. 

This occurred with basically all of my tried combinations of foundation, priming and setting powder products. It was also a bit difficult to touch up because it does dry quite quickly.
faceoff_negative.headline: Great coverage but creases after a few hours
